The following software must be installed:

* A current, supported [[release of Go|https://go.dev/doc/devel/release]],
* [[Fossil|https://fossil-scm.org/]],
* [[Git|https://git-scm.org/]] (most dependencies are accessible via Git only).

Make sure that the software is in your path, e.g. via:
```sh
export PATH=$PATH:/usr/local/go/bin
export PATH=$PATH:$(go env GOPATH)/bin
```

The internal build tool needs the following software tools.
They can be installed / updated via the build tool itself: ``go run tools/devtools/devtools.go``{=sh}.

Otherwise you can install the software by hand:

* [[shadow|https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/go/analysis/passes/shadow]] via ``go install golang.org/x/tools/go/analysis/passes/shadow/cmd/shadow@latest``{=sh},
* [[unparam|https://mvdan.cc/unparam]][^[[GitHub|https://github.com/mvdan/unparam]]] via ``go install mvdan.cc/unparam@latest``{=sh},
* [[staticcheck|https://staticcheck.io/]] via ``go install honnef.co/go/tools/cmd/staticcheck@latest``{=sh},
* [[deadcode|https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/cmd/deadcode]] via ``go install golang.org/x/tools/cmd/deadcode@latest``{=sh},
* [[errcheck|https://github.com/kisielk/errcheck]] via ``go install github.com/kisielk/errcheck@latest``{=sh},
* [[revive|https://revive.run]] via ``go install github.com/mgechev/revive@latest``{=sh},
* [[govulncheck|https://golang.org/x/vuln/cmd/govulncheck]] via ``go install golang.org/x/vuln/cmd/govulncheck@latest``{=sh},
